erving the artistic design elements<br>\r\n- Developing a maintainable component system for reusable hand-drawn elements<br>', '- Implemented custom SVG path animations with Framer Motion for realistic drawing effects<br>\r\n- Created a paper texture component system with configurable styles and behaviors<br>\r\n- Utilized Next.js 14 with client-side optimizations for smooth animation performance<br>\r\n- Designed modular UI components with consistent hand-drawn aesthetics<br>\r\n- Applied lazy loading and code splitting for optimal resource management<br>\r\n- Built accessible interactive elements with ARIA attributes while maintaining visual appeal<br>\r\n- Established TypeScript interfaces for all custom components to ensure type safety<br>', '2025-03-01', '2025-03-07 13:44:55', '2025-03-27 02:56:12', 'Completed', '2025-03-07', NULL, '[]'),
(8, 'Sketchfolio - Interactive Hand-Drawn Art Portfolio', 'Web Development', 'A modern interactive portfolio built with Next.js, TypeScript, and Anime.js featuring hand-drawn animations, interactive drawing experiences, paper physics simulations, and a comprehensive artwork gallery.', '<section class=\"project-header\">\r\nA modern interactive portfolio website featuring hand-drawn animations and interactive experiences. Built with Next.js and TypeScript, Sketchfolio combines artistic design with technical innovation to create an immersive showcase for creative work. The project implements various animation techniques and interactive elements to engage visitors and display artwork in a unique way.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key Features:</h2><br>\r\n\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Drawing Animations: SVG path animations with staged reveals and sequenced drawing effects<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Interactive Drawing: Canvas-based drawing tools allowing visitors to create their own artwork<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Paper Physics Simulation: Interactive paper scraps that respond to physics using Matter.js<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Artwork Gallery: Filterable gallery with categories and modal detail views<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Portfolio Projects: Showcase of creative work with expandable project details<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Interactive Path Drawing: Combined animations with user drawing capabilities<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Responsive Design: Mobile-first approach ensuring perfect display across all device sizes<br><br>\r\n\r\n<h2>Technical Implementation:</h2><br>\r\n\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Built with Next.js 15.2.1 and React 19.0.0 for modern, performant web development<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ TypeScript for type-safe component development and better code quality<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Anime.js for smooth, sophisticated SVG path animations and transitions<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Matter.js for realistic physics simulations in the Paper Physics component<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Framer Motion for UI animations and mobile menu transitions<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ CSS with custom animations and responsive breakpoints for mobile compatibility<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ IntersectionObserver API for scroll-based animations and lazy loading<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Deployment configuration with Netlify for continuous integration<br><br>\r\n\r\nThe project demonstrates advanced animation techniques and interactive experiences while maintaining accessibility and performance. The hand-drawn aesthetic is consistently applied throughout the UI, creating a cohesive and engaging experience for portfolio visitors.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<h2>Project Links:</h2><br>\r\n\r\n&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp â€¢ Live Demo: <a href=\"https://sketchfolio.netlify.app/\" target=\"_blank\">Sketchfolio Interactive Portfolio</a><br>\r\n&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp â€¢ Technologies: Next.js, React, TypeScript, Anime.js, Matter.js<br>\r\n&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp â€¢ Version: 1.0.0<br><br>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"date\">An immersive interactive portfolio that brings hand-drawn artwork to life through animations and interactive experiences, showcasing both artistic creativity and technical implementation.</p>\r\n</section>', 'Images/projects/Screenshot 2025-03-08 163019.png', '[\"Images\\/gallery\\/photo_2025-03-08_16-34-12.jpg\",\"Images\\/gallery\\/photo_2025-03-08_16-34-17.jpg\",\"Images\\/gallery\\/photo_2025-03-08_16-34-19.jpg\",\"Images\\/gallery\\/Screenshot 2025-03-08 163028.png\",\"Images\\/gallery\\/Screenshot 2025-03-08 163036.png\",\"Images\\/gallery\\/Screenshot 2025-03-08 163049.png\",\"Images\\/gallery\\/Screenshot 2025-03-08 163101.png\",\"Images\\/gallery\\/Screenshot 2025-03-08 163119.png\",\"Images\\/gallery\\/Screenshot 2025-03-08 163140.png\"]', 'Next.js 15.2, React 19.0, TypeScript, Anime.js, Matter.js, Framer Motion, CSS Modules, React Intersection Observer, Netlify', '- Creating fluid SVG path animations that work consistently across different browsers and devices<br>\r\n- Implementing a responsive design system for interactive components that adapts to touch and mouse input<br>\r\n- Building physics simulations that perform well on both desktop and mobile devices<br>\r\n- Developing a consistent hand-drawn aesthetic throughout the UI while maintaining usability<br>\r\n- Optimizing animation performance to avoid layout thrashing and maintain smooth framerates<br>\r\n- Ensuring accessibility standards despite complex visual animations and interactive elements<br>\r\n- Managing complex state between animation and interactive drawing components without conflicts<br>', '- Implemented progressive enhancement approach for animations using Anime.js with fallbacks for basic browsers<br>\r\n- Created a responsive component system with dynamic sizing based on viewport and interaction method detection<br>\r\n- Utilized Matter.js with optimized configurations and throttling for performance-intensive physics simulations<br>\r\n- Designed a cohesive visual language with SVG patterns and consistent styling across all components<br>\r\n- Applied debouncing and requestAnimationFrame techniques to optimize animation performance<br>\r\n- Built accessible interactive components with proper ARIA attributes and keyboard navigation support<br>\r\n- Developed a component architecture that separates animation logic from interactive features for better maintainability<br>\r\n- Established efficient event handling for touch and mouse interactions to ensure smooth drawing experiences<br>', '2025-03-06', '2025-03-08 16:34:32', '2025-03-27 02:55:36', 'Completed', '2025-03-08', NULL, '[]'),
(9, 'SaaS Dashboard - Modern Analytics & Admin Panel', 'Web Development', 'A modern dashboard template built with React, Material-UI, and Chart.js featuring interactive data visualization with mock data, theme customization, and a comprehensive admin interface design that demonstrates frontend capabilities without backend depend', '<section class=\"project-header\">\r\nA modern SaaS dashboard template featuring a clean, professional design with interactive data visualization and comprehensive admin controls. Built with React and modern UI libraries, this frontend implementation uses mock data to showcase a realistic dashboard experience without requiring a backend.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key Features:</h2><br>\r\n\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Dynamic Dashboard: Interactive charts and graphs with simulated data visualization<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Theme Customization: Elegant dark/light mode switching with customizable color schemes<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ User Interface: Mockup of user management and role-based access controls<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Analytics Dashboard: Sample data analysis tools with customizable metrics<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Widget System: Customizable dashboard widgets with drag-and-drop capabilities<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Data Tables: Advanced filtering, sorting, and pagination with sample datasets<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Responsive Layout: Fully adaptive design optimized for all device sizes<br><br>\r\n\r\n<h2>Technical Implementation:</h2><br>\r\n\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Built with React 18 for modern, efficient component architecture<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Material-UI components for consistent and professional UI elements<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Redux Toolkit for centralized UI state management<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Chart.js and D3.js for sophisticated data visualization with mock data<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Styled-components for dynamic and maintainable styling<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ JSON mock data structured to simulate API responses<br>\r\n&nbsp â€¢ Modular architecture designed for easy backend integration in the future<br>\r\n&nb